Text.SourceString: Yes, <PlayerName>$player</>!//<portrait=normal>I’ve been meaning to meet you. My name is <NPCName>Millie</>.//It’s so exciting to have people moving in.
Text.LocalizedString: Yes, <PlayerName>$player</>!//<portrait=normal>I’ve been meaning to meet you. My name is <NPCName>Millie</>.//It’s so exciting to have people moving in.

Text.SourceString: Have you met everyone?
Text.LocalizedString: Have you met everyone?

Text.SourceString: Should I sort my recyclables, you think?
Text.LocalizedString: Should I sort my recyclables, you think?

Text.SourceString: Nah, not today. Maybe I’ll do it once the recycling center is fixed up.
Text.LocalizedString: Nah, not today. Maybe I’ll do it once the recycling center is fixed up.

Text.SourceString: When we have a community garden, I’ll plant a lot of flowers.//<portrait=annoyed>Won’t be able to help out with gardening except on Thursdays, though.
Text.LocalizedString: When we have a community garden, I’ll plant a lot of flowers.//<portrait=annoyed>Won’t be able to help out with gardening except on Thursdays, though.

Text.SourceString: I like hanging out at work, so I usually stay here until I get sleepy.
Text.LocalizedString: I like hanging out at work, so I usually stay here until I get sleepy.

Text.SourceString: Why would I hang out at home when the library is the heart of Starlet Town? Exactly, there's no reason!
Text.LocalizedString: Why would I hang out at home when the library is the heart of Starlet Town? Exactly, there's no reason!

Text.SourceString: We have a large selection of books here. Feel free to immerse yourself in this ocean of wisdom.
Text.LocalizedString: We have a large selection of books here. Feel free to immerse yourself in this ocean of wisdom.

Text.SourceString: This job is like winning the lottery for a bookworm like me.//<portrait=normal>I get to devour novels while making sure they're well-organized. A double treat!
Text.LocalizedString: This job is like winning the lottery for a bookworm like me.//<portrait=normal>I get to devour novels while making sure they're well-organized. A double treat!

Text.SourceString: Hmm… I think I’ll go to the forest to gather some fresh fruit on Thursday.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm… I think I’ll go to the forest to gather some fresh fruit on Thursday.

Text.SourceString: Oh! Or maybe I should transform into a beach-loving pelican!//Pack a lunch, grab some books, and bask in the glory of the sun... decisions, decisions.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh! Or maybe I should transform into a beach-loving pelican!//Pack a lunch, grab some books, and bask in the glory of the sun... decisions, decisions.

Text.SourceString: I’m grateful for all the donations the library receives. Not just books, you know. We get plenty of money as well.//<portrait=normal>Some donations even come in from neighboring islands.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m grateful for all the donations the library receives. Not just books, you know. We get plenty of money as well.//<portrait=normal>Some donations even come in from neighboring islands.

Text.SourceString: Biology has always interested me, especially wildlife.
Text.LocalizedString: Biology has always interested me, especially wildlife.

Text.SourceString: I take Thursdays off.//I’ll be at the library first thing tomorrow morning.
Text.LocalizedString: I take Thursdays off.//I’ll be at the library first thing tomorrow morning.

Text.SourceString: Oh gosh… Sometimes I read for too long. Then I get that dizzy feeling when I stand up… Do you know what I’m talking about?//<portrait=concerned>Good thing my housemate is a doctor.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh gosh… Sometimes I read for too long. Then I get that dizzy feeling when I stand up… Do you know what I’m talking about?//<portrait=concerned>Good thing my housemate is a doctor.

Text.SourceString: She doesn’t give me a discount at the clinic, though.//Should I ask for it?
Text.LocalizedString: She doesn’t give me a discount at the clinic, though.//Should I ask for it?

Text.SourceString: How’s life at the farm, you adventurous sword-toting eagle?
Text.LocalizedString: How’s life at the farm, you adventurous sword-toting eagle?

Text.SourceString: I help the mayor as much as I can with festivals, fairs, and such.//I wish there were more ways to serve our sweet town…
Text.LocalizedString: I help the mayor as much as I can with festivals, fairs, and such.//I wish there were more ways to serve our sweet town…

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Randy</> asked me to collect some articles for the kids. Additional reading and such.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Randy</> asked me to collect some articles for the kids. Additional reading and such.

Text.SourceString: First editions are incredibly valuable! Well, to me, anyway. Generally, that’s where the author’s original ideas shine the brightest…alongside the typos.//<portrait=happy>Heh heh!
Text.LocalizedString: First editions are incredibly valuable! Well, to me, anyway. Generally, that’s where the author’s original ideas shine the brightest…alongside the typos.//<portrait=happy>Heh heh!

Text.SourceString: Imagine, being the first to explore the undiscovered territories of an author's mind...
Text.LocalizedString: Imagine, being the first to explore the undiscovered territories of an author's mind...

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Scott</> doesn’t work on weekends.//Honestly, I don’t think he needs to!
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Scott</> doesn’t work on weekends.//Honestly, I don’t think he needs to!

Text.SourceString: We have the museum under control.
Text.LocalizedString: We have the museum under control.

Text.SourceString: Romance novels are my ultimate guilty pleasure. The good ones can really draw you in emotionally.
Text.LocalizedString: Romance novels are my ultimate guilty pleasure. The good ones can really draw you in emotionally.

Text.SourceString: I love worn-out books. To me, they speak of love and appreciation.
Text.LocalizedString: I love worn-out books. To me, they speak of love and appreciation.

Text.SourceString: That’s what books aspire to, right? To be read over and over again by many people.
Text.LocalizedString: That’s what books aspire to, right? To be read over and over again by many people.

Text.SourceString: Oh! An endless sea of books to sail and just a tiny ship of time.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh! An endless sea of books to sail and just a tiny ship of time.

Text.SourceString: I once read that some plants survive two seasons…//That must be very economical for business, I would think. Less money spent on seeds.
Text.LocalizedString: I once read that some plants survive two seasons…//That must be very economical for business, I would think. Less money spent on seeds.

Text.SourceString: If you have anything to donate, please send it over to the museum. We have a donation box there.
Text.LocalizedString: If you have anything to donate, please send it over to the museum. We have a donation box there.

Text.SourceString: Once you put a donation in the box, I file all the information before we start the inspection process. When that’s done, <NPCName>Scott</> takes care of the rest.
Text.LocalizedString: Once you put a donation in the box, I file all the information before we start the inspection process. When that’s done, <NPCName>Scott</> takes care of the rest.

Text.SourceString: When I pass by your farm, I tell you, it's got the best sunset view in town.
Text.LocalizedString: When I pass by your farm, I tell you, it's got the best sunset view in town.

Text.SourceString: Your farm is like a little gem in our community.//But it's got to be as much work as organizing a town festival!
Text.LocalizedString: Your farm is like a little gem in our community.//But it's got to be as much work as organizing a town festival!

Text.SourceString: I like to think of myself as the captain of the library and museum ship here in town.
Text.LocalizedString: I like to think of myself as the captain of the library and museum ship here in town.

Text.SourceString: What’s a butterfly like you doing in here, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: What’s a butterfly like you doing in here, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: What’s a butterfly like you doing in here, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: What’s a butterfly like you doing in here, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: Are we finally going to discuss <Italic>The Tale of Dulcans</>?//<portrait=normal>Have you finished reading the series yet?
Text.LocalizedString: Are we finally going to discuss <Italic>The Tale of Dulcans</>?//<portrait=normal>Have you finished reading the series yet?

Text.SourceString: I'm thinking about trying diving tomorrow, unless I get too caught up watching the birds.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm thinking about trying diving tomorrow, unless I get too caught up watching the birds.

Text.SourceString: Time certainly flies when you’re having fun.
Text.LocalizedString: Time certainly flies when you’re having fun.

Text.SourceString: I’ve been trying to write one article the whole day.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been trying to write one article the whole day.

Text.SourceString: My brain feels like it's stuck in a traffic jam today.//Can't find a worthwhile thought to save my life.
Text.LocalizedString: My brain feels like it's stuck in a traffic jam today.//Can't find a worthwhile thought to save my life.

Text.SourceString: The Cherry Blossom Festival always fills me with joy.//<portrait=normal>It's the blooming trees, the community spirit...it's just perfect.
Text.LocalizedString: The Cherry Blossom Festival always fills me with joy.//<portrait=normal>It's the blooming trees, the community spirit...it's just perfect.

Text.SourceString: Are you planting any melons on your farm?//Oh, right! Melons are a Summer crop, aren’t they?
Text.LocalizedString: Are you planting any melons on your farm?//Oh, right! Melons are a Summer crop, aren’t they?

Text.SourceString: Every Spring, I always think of poor <NPCName>Charles</>. He gets a case of the sneezes as soon as the flowers start to bloom.
Text.LocalizedString: Every Spring, I always think of poor <NPCName>Charles</>. He gets a case of the sneezes as soon as the flowers start to bloom.

Text.SourceString: I’m starting to see a lot more lizards out. Even my lizard, Tin, is a lot more active now.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m starting to see a lot more lizards out. Even my lizard, Tin, is a lot more active now.

Text.SourceString: Tin likes to be out and about. He rarely stays inside his little glass room, that one.//An adventurer!
Text.LocalizedString: Tin likes to be out and about. He rarely stays inside his little glass room, that one.//An adventurer!

Text.SourceString: I can feel the air slowly warming up.
Text.LocalizedString: I can feel the air slowly warming up.

Text.SourceString: Is it too early to start looking for melons at <NPCName>Sam</>’s? Hmm…
Text.LocalizedString: Is it too early to start looking for melons at <NPCName>Sam</>’s? Hmm…

Text.SourceString: Summer can get pretty stuffy.//<portrait=happy>Thankfully, I live in Garden Lane. It’s so green and lush. Once you open the window – wah… The breeze is amazing!//<portrait=normal>It’s the base camp for bugs, though. I bet you could catch a lot of them there, am I right?
Text.LocalizedString: Summer can get pretty stuffy.//<portrait=happy>Thankfully, I live in Garden Lane. It’s so green and lush. Once you open the window – wah… The breeze is amazing!//<portrait=normal>It’s the base camp for bugs, though. I bet you could catch a lot of them there, am I right?

Text.SourceString: I've been thinking about baking some cookies for the kids at the library, instead of getting them from <NPCName>Sam</>'s.//<portrait=normal>It's a fun idea but in this heat, I don’t think it’s worth the money saved, right?
Text.LocalizedString: I've been thinking about baking some cookies for the kids at the library, instead of getting them from <NPCName>Sam</>'s.//<portrait=normal>It's a fun idea but in this heat, I don’t think it’s worth the money saved, right?

Text.SourceString: Pufferfish is going to have a stand at this year’s Beach Cleanup Festival. *sighs* It’s kind of hard to say no to them.
Text.LocalizedString: Pufferfish is going to have a stand at this year’s Beach Cleanup Festival. *sighs* It’s kind of hard to say no to them.

Text.SourceString: We ran out of melons yesterday. I wonder if <NPCName>Sam</> still has some…
Text.LocalizedString: We ran out of melons yesterday. I wonder if <NPCName>Sam</> still has some…

Text.SourceString: The grass is looking kind of sad, isn’t it? That lot next to my house looks so dry.//So yellow… Poor things.
Text.LocalizedString: The grass is looking kind of sad, isn’t it? That lot next to my house looks so dry.//So yellow… Poor things.

Text.SourceString: I feel like I romanticize Fall a bit too much.//<portrait=blushing>But don’t you agree there’s something beautiful about writing a novel as the leaves fall around you?
Text.LocalizedString: I feel like I romanticize Fall a bit too much.//<portrait=blushing>But don’t you agree there’s something beautiful about writing a novel as the leaves fall around you?

Text.SourceString: I’m always inspired to write more in Fall. I wonder why that is…
Text.LocalizedString: I’m always inspired to write more in Fall. I wonder why that is…

Text.SourceString: I’m craving some ramen right now. Any kind of ramen. Mmm…
Text.LocalizedString: I’m craving some ramen right now. Any kind of ramen. Mmm…

Text.SourceString: I’ve been communicating a lot with Beluga Bay, since we’re the one hosting the Harvest Festival.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been communicating a lot with Beluga Bay, since we’re the one hosting the Harvest Festival.

Text.SourceString: Mayor <NPCName>Connor</> is really itching to win the harvest display this year…and me too!
Text.LocalizedString: Mayor <NPCName>Connor</> is really itching to win the harvest display this year…and me too!

Text.SourceString: The Harvest Festival is one of the more complicated festivals to set up, but I always have so much fun while it’s happening.//<portrait=happy>It feels like a reward for all the hard work!
Text.LocalizedString: The Harvest Festival is one of the more complicated festivals to set up, but I always have so much fun while it’s happening.//<portrait=happy>It feels like a reward for all the hard work!

Text.SourceString: Until we meet again, sweet, sweet Fall air…
Text.LocalizedString: Until we meet again, sweet, sweet Fall air…

Text.SourceString: Ah, dear Fall. How I’ve missed you.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, dear Fall. How I’ve missed you.

Text.SourceString: Now it’s Winter, I can finally relax a bit.
Text.LocalizedString: Now it’s Winter, I can finally relax a bit.

Text.SourceString: I’ve been eating too much ramen, but I can’t help myself!//<portrait=happy>I love some soupy goodness in the frigid Winter.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been eating too much ramen, but I can’t help myself!//<portrait=happy>I love some soupy goodness in the frigid Winter.

Text.SourceString: I wonder how many great authors write in the dead of Winter.//It feels like the perfect season for writing. I prefer writing in Fall myself, though.
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder how many great authors write in the dead of Winter.//It feels like the perfect season for writing. I prefer writing in Fall myself, though.

Text.SourceString: A steaming cup of coffee or tea, something to write with, the snow fluttering, and the fireplace roaring…//<portrait=blushing>Doesn’t that sound great?
Text.LocalizedString: A steaming cup of coffee or tea, something to write with, the snow fluttering, and the fireplace roaring…//<portrait=blushing>Doesn’t that sound great?

Text.SourceString: The best thing about having a doctor as a roommate is I can just ask her to do my checkups at home.//<portrait=normal>I still have to pay her, though, which is fair enough.
Text.LocalizedString: The best thing about having a doctor as a roommate is I can just ask her to do my checkups at home.//<portrait=normal>I still have to pay her, though, which is fair enough.

Text.SourceString: It’s the Cherry Blossom Festival tomorrow.//I think I’ll bring some vegetables… I’m not sure yet.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s the Cherry Blossom Festival tomorrow.//I think I’ll bring some vegetables… I’m not sure yet.

Text.SourceString: I’m like a well-prepared scout.//I got my flu shot early this year, so I’m fully equipped for the sniffle season.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m like a well-prepared scout.//I got my flu shot early this year, so I’m fully equipped for the sniffle season.

Text.SourceString: A lot of people get the sniffles this time of year.
Text.LocalizedString: A lot of people get the sniffles this time of year.

Text.SourceString: Oh my! Is this the last week of Spring already?
Text.LocalizedString: Oh my! Is this the last week of Spring already?

Text.SourceString: I need to get my Summer reading ready!
Text.LocalizedString: I need to get my Summer reading ready!

Text.SourceString: I avoid the beach during Summer because the heat can be too much for me.
Text.LocalizedString: I avoid the beach during Summer because the heat can be too much for me.

Text.SourceString: I prefer the beach in Winter, to be honest… Thick jacket and chilly wind.//Best combo.
Text.LocalizedString: I prefer the beach in Winter, to be honest… Thick jacket and chilly wind.//Best combo.

Text.SourceString: I wonder if <NPCName>Sam</>’s is open today. I’m running out of milk and fruit.
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder if <NPCName>Sam</>’s is open today. I’m running out of milk and fruit.

Text.SourceString: I hope <NPCName>Sam</> has blueberries. I’m craving some Summer fruit pies!
Text.LocalizedString: I hope <NPCName>Sam</> has blueberries. I’m craving some Summer fruit pies!

Text.SourceString: I love writing and reading. Sucker for romance fiction here, but I’ll read anything.//<portrait=normal>A good book is a good book.
Text.LocalizedString: I love writing and reading. Sucker for romance fiction here, but I’ll read anything.//<portrait=normal>A good book is a good book.

Text.SourceString: I avoid the beach during Summer because the heat can be too much for me.
Text.LocalizedString: I avoid the beach during Summer because the heat can be too much for me.

Text.SourceString: I prefer the beach in Winter, to be honest… Thick jacket and chilly wind.//Best combo.
Text.LocalizedString: I prefer the beach in Winter, to be honest… Thick jacket and chilly wind.//Best combo.

Text.SourceString: It’s freezing today.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s freezing today.

Text.SourceString: I’m looking forward to Spring.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m looking forward to Spring.

Text.SourceString: I’ll miss the snow, though.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ll miss the snow, though.

Text.SourceString: Do I do things differently in Winter?//Hmm, good question.
Text.LocalizedString: Do I do things differently in Winter?//Hmm, good question.

Text.SourceString: I guess not really.//<portrait=normal>I love my library life, but I do enjoy the occasional beach visit too.
Text.LocalizedString: I guess not really.//<portrait=normal>I love my library life, but I do enjoy the occasional beach visit too.

Text.SourceString: Please be careful with the books here.//Some of them are very old and delicate, so wet hands can damage them.
Text.LocalizedString: Please be careful with the books here.//Some of them are very old and delicate, so wet hands can damage them.

Text.SourceString: I plan to channel today's rain into a writing marathon.//<portrait=normal>It makes me feel contemplative.
Text.LocalizedString: I plan to channel today's rain into a writing marathon.//<portrait=normal>It makes me feel contemplative.

Text.SourceString: Have you noticed the weather channel isn’t always accurate?//It makes it hard to plan my days out.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you noticed the weather channel isn’t always accurate?//It makes it hard to plan my days out.

Text.SourceString: The weather channel isn’t always accurate.
Text.LocalizedString: The weather channel isn’t always accurate.

Text.SourceString: I hope it stops raining soon.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope it stops raining soon.

Text.SourceString: I don’t feel like going anywhere today.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t feel like going anywhere today.

Text.SourceString: Excuse me.
Text.LocalizedString: Excuse me.

Text.SourceString: Excuse me.
Text.LocalizedString: Excuse me.

Text.SourceString: Does it feel like it storms more in Spring?
Text.LocalizedString: Does it feel like it storms more in Spring?

Text.SourceString: Because it sure does feel like it to me.
Text.LocalizedString: Because it sure does feel like it to me.

Text.SourceString: Does it feel like it storms more in Summer?
Text.LocalizedString: Does it feel like it storms more in Summer?

Text.SourceString: I can't be the only one who thinks that, right?
Text.LocalizedString: I can't be the only one who thinks that, right?

Text.SourceString: Today's snowfall is inspiring me to write.//<portrait=normal>It makes me feel contemplative.
Text.LocalizedString: Today's snowfall is inspiring me to write.//<portrait=normal>It makes me feel contemplative.

Text.SourceString: I wonder if <NPCName>Sam</>’s is open today. I’m running out of milk and fruit.
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder if <NPCName>Sam</>’s is open today. I’m running out of milk and fruit.

Text.SourceString: You can read about fish here. There are plenty of informative books about when to catch them.
Text.LocalizedString: You can read about fish here. There are plenty of informative books about when to catch them.

Text.SourceString: Are you looking for a specific book?
Text.LocalizedString: Are you looking for a specific book?

Text.SourceString: The farming books are over there.
Text.LocalizedString: The farming books are over there.

Text.SourceString: Once you donate a certain number of items, you’re welcome to collect your reward.
Text.LocalizedString: Once you donate a certain number of items, you’re welcome to collect your reward.

Text.SourceString: Don’t you just love the smell of old books?
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t you just love the smell of old books?

Text.SourceString: When we receive a new shipment of books, I like to do the unpacking myself.
Text.LocalizedString: When we receive a new shipment of books, I like to do the unpacking myself.

Text.SourceString: We got several donations from <NPCName>Zarah</>.//She worked with us a couple of times to find some lost treasures.
Text.LocalizedString: We got several donations from <NPCName>Zarah</>.//She worked with us a couple of times to find some lost treasures.

Text.SourceString: How’s your lizard knowledge, <PlayerName>$player</>? Tin hasn’t been showing up much lately.//I’m getting a little worried.
Text.LocalizedString: How’s your lizard knowledge, <PlayerName>$player</>? Tin hasn’t been showing up much lately.//I’m getting a little worried.

Text.SourceString: Tin isn’t exactly a pet, more of a spontaneous lizard visitor who likes to hang out with me.
Text.LocalizedString: Tin isn’t exactly a pet, more of a spontaneous lizard visitor who likes to hang out with me.

Text.SourceString: I get here before 10 am almost every day. I like to be punctual.
Text.LocalizedString: I get here before 10 am almost every day. I like to be punctual.

Text.SourceString: The lights here are funny. I think the wiring must be old and needs some work.//<portrait=annoyed>Sometimes they go off and on by themselves.
Text.LocalizedString: The lights here are funny. I think the wiring must be old and needs some work.//<portrait=annoyed>Sometimes they go off and on by themselves.

Text.SourceString: You can see all kinds of butterflies and birds from here.
Text.LocalizedString: You can see all kinds of butterflies and birds from here.

Text.SourceString: On your way to town, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: On your way to town, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: It feels too cold to go to the beach. I think I’ll go home after this.
Text.LocalizedString: It feels too cold to go to the beach. I think I’ll go home after this.

Text.SourceString: Thankfully, it’s nice and warm in here.
Text.LocalizedString: Thankfully, it’s nice and warm in here.

Text.SourceString: I’m here to pick up some fresh fish for dinner.//I’m thinking about cooking fish tacos tonight… Hmm?
Text.LocalizedString: I’m here to pick up some fresh fish for dinner.//I’m thinking about cooking fish tacos tonight… Hmm?

Text.SourceString: Or I could just buy a premade meal.//It’s much easier, and I know it’ll be good. Guaranteed.
Text.LocalizedString: Or I could just buy a premade meal.//It’s much easier, and I know it’ll be good. Guaranteed.

Text.SourceString: Cooking can be fun. You can get all the fancy gadgets and try out new recipes.
Text.LocalizedString: Cooking can be fun. You can get all the fancy gadgets and try out new recipes.

Text.SourceString: Going diving, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Going diving, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: I should go home soon. I need time to make dinner.
Text.LocalizedString: I should go home soon. I need time to make dinner.

Text.SourceString: I’m cooking fish tonight!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m cooking fish tonight!

Text.SourceString: We have a large selection of books here. Take your time browsing!
Text.LocalizedString: We have a large selection of books here. Take your time browsing!

Text.SourceString: I’m hoping we get more first editions!//<portrait=normal>Book restoration is a hobby of mine.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m hoping we get more first editions!//<portrait=normal>Book restoration is a hobby of mine.

Text.SourceString: I tell you, when I see a beat-up first edition in need of care, it makes my week.
Text.LocalizedString: I tell you, when I see a beat-up first edition in need of care, it makes my week.

Text.SourceString: How’s your week shaping up, you magnificent monarch of productivity?//<portrait=happy>Good? Good!
Text.LocalizedString: How’s your week shaping up, you magnificent monarch of productivity?//<portrait=happy>Good? Good!

Text.SourceString: Reading truly is a marvel. How else can we connect so intimately with people across time?
Text.LocalizedString: Reading truly is a marvel. How else can we connect so intimately with people across time?

Text.SourceString: Have you read anything interesting lately, <PlayerName>$player</>?//My book list is always open for recommendations.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you read anything interesting lately, <PlayerName>$player</>?//My book list is always open for recommendations.

Text.SourceString: Tomorrow is my recycling day! Scheduling chores helps me remember to do them.
Text.LocalizedString: Tomorrow is my recycling day! Scheduling chores helps me remember to do them.

Text.SourceString: I don’t often sort my recyclables, though.//<portrait=normal>I’ll make a point to do it when the recycling center is fixed up.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t often sort my recyclables, though.//<portrait=normal>I’ll make a point to do it when the recycling center is fixed up.

Text.SourceString: I like to start the day slowly with a book and a warm mug of coffee.
Text.LocalizedString: I like to start the day slowly with a book and a warm mug of coffee.

Text.SourceString: My favorite way to kickstart the day is with a captivating book and a steaming mug of ambition... I mean coffee!
Text.LocalizedString: My favorite way to kickstart the day is with a captivating book and a steaming mug of ambition... I mean coffee!

Text.SourceString: I love restoring books in my spare time.//Making covers, taking care of old books… Little things like that make my week.
Text.LocalizedString: I love restoring books in my spare time.//Making covers, taking care of old books… Little things like that make my week.

Text.SourceString: We have several shelves of first editions here. They’re the library’s most precious assets, at least to me.//<portrait=happy>Some are even signed by the author!
Text.LocalizedString: We have several shelves of first editions here. They’re the library’s most precious assets, at least to me.//<portrait=happy>Some are even signed by the author!

Text.SourceString: Earlier, I spotted some crows near your farm.//I hope you have scarecrows, <PlayerName>$player</>. Those birds eat crops, after all.
Text.LocalizedString: Earlier, I spotted some crows near your farm.//I hope you have scarecrows, <PlayerName>$player</>. Those birds eat crops, after all.

Text.SourceString: Oh! I also saw some parrots!
Text.LocalizedString: Oh! I also saw some parrots!

Text.SourceString: The townsfolk are quite eager to help out around town, especially with changing the seasonal decorations.
Text.LocalizedString: The townsfolk are quite eager to help out around town, especially with changing the seasonal decorations.

Text.SourceString: Though I must admit, the decorations are my favorite part too!
Text.LocalizedString: Though I must admit, the decorations are my favorite part too!

Text.SourceString: This island’s wildlife never ceases to amaze me. So much gorgeous fauna!
Text.LocalizedString: This island’s wildlife never ceases to amaze me. So much gorgeous fauna!

Text.SourceString: I know I talk a lot about birds, but I’m fond of butterflies as well.//<portrait=happy>All lovely winged creatures captivate me!
Text.LocalizedString: I know I talk a lot about birds, but I’m fond of butterflies as well.//<portrait=happy>All lovely winged creatures captivate me!

Text.SourceString: I have a good life, all things considered.//I want for very little.
Text.LocalizedString: I have a good life, all things considered.//I want for very little.

Text.SourceString: The local legends of this island are rather captivating.//You ought to read up on them, if you haven’t already.
Text.LocalizedString: The local legends of this island are rather captivating.//You ought to read up on them, if you haven’t already.

Text.SourceString: I’m sure a lot of our customs will become clearer with them in mind!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m sure a lot of our customs will become clearer with them in mind!

Text.SourceString: Let me know if you ever want a book recommendation.//<portrait=normal>I often suggest books to townsfolk!
Text.LocalizedString: Let me know if you ever want a book recommendation.//<portrait=normal>I often suggest books to townsfolk!

Text.SourceString: Now, what’s a free-roaming butterfly like you doing in here, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Now, what’s a free-roaming butterfly like you doing in here, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: I suppose you know how it feels to yearn for a change of pace.//You left everything behind to come here, after all.
Text.LocalizedString: I suppose you know how it feels to yearn for a change of pace.//You left everything behind to come here, after all.

Text.SourceString: Once in a while, I get invested in a series of novels, only to find the author hasn’t completed it.
Text.LocalizedString: Once in a while, I get invested in a series of novels, only to find the author hasn’t completed it.

Text.SourceString: It’s even worse when it seems like the series will never be finished… What do I do then?
Text.LocalizedString: It’s even worse when it seems like the series will never be finished… What do I do then?

Text.SourceString: Hmm… After giving it some thought, I don’t think I have a favorite bird.//<portrait=normal>I love all birds equally!
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm… After giving it some thought, I don’t think I have a favorite bird.//<portrait=normal>I love all birds equally!

Text.SourceString: Even crows! They get a bad rap, but they’re fascinating, intelligent creatures.
Text.LocalizedString: Even crows! They get a bad rap, but they’re fascinating, intelligent creatures.

Text.SourceString: <PlayerName>$player</>… Do you think I talk about books too much?
Text.LocalizedString: <PlayerName>$player</>… Do you think I talk about books too much?

Text.SourceString: I… Hmm. No, I suppose I don’t. My apologies for bothering you.
Text.LocalizedString: I… Hmm. No, I suppose I don’t. My apologies for bothering you.

Special.SourceString: Maybe a little. Don’t you have more to say?
Special.LocalizedString: Maybe a little. Don’t you have more to say?

Text.SourceString: That’s so sweet of you to say! Thank you. I needed to hear that.
Text.LocalizedString: That’s so sweet of you to say! Thank you. I needed to hear that.

Special.SourceString: No. It makes you happy, so it’s not too much.
Special.LocalizedString: No. It makes you happy, so it’s not too much.

Text.SourceString: I don’t go to the forest much.//I suppose I’m not much of a hiker.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t go to the forest much.//I suppose I’m not much of a hiker.

Text.SourceString: I prefer to walk on proper roads.//But in your line of work, walking through the dirt seems unavoidable!
Text.LocalizedString: I prefer to walk on proper roads.//But in your line of work, walking through the dirt seems unavoidable!

Text.SourceString: I must say, I’m counting the days until Spring.
Text.LocalizedString: I must say, I’m counting the days until Spring.

Text.SourceString: But, I'll miss the twinkle of the snow...
Text.LocalizedString: But, I'll miss the twinkle of the snow...

Text.SourceString: Watch out for caterpillars, <PlayerName>$player</>. Try not to step on them! They’re everywhere.//Be the observant hawk that you are!
Text.LocalizedString: Watch out for caterpillars, <PlayerName>$player</>. Try not to step on them! They’re everywhere.//Be the observant hawk that you are!

Text.SourceString: Can you imagine being on the front line of current world affairs and getting to report on them?
Text.LocalizedString: Can you imagine being on the front line of current world affairs and getting to report on them?

Text.SourceString: I wish I could do that kind of journalism.
Text.LocalizedString: I wish I could do that kind of journalism.

Text.SourceString: I was stung by a bug yesterday. Don’t know what it was. All of a sudden, I felt my hand burning…//Thankfully, I was just in front of my house, so I went in and took care of it right away.
Text.LocalizedString: I was stung by a bug yesterday. Don’t know what it was. All of a sudden, I felt my hand burning…//Thankfully, I was just in front of my house, so I went in and took care of it right away.

Text.SourceString: I was minding my own business, bird-watching and whatnot.//<portrait=angry>I refuse to wear bug repellent. I do… I won’t do it.//If it costs me my body, then so be it.
Text.LocalizedString: I was minding my own business, bird-watching and whatnot.//<portrait=angry>I refuse to wear bug repellent. I do… I won’t do it.//If it costs me my body, then so be it.

Text.SourceString: I still have some donated books in the back that need sorting.
Text.LocalizedString: I still have some donated books in the back that need sorting.

Text.SourceString: I need to find time to write this weekend… Humph.
Text.LocalizedString: I need to find time to write this weekend… Humph.

Text.SourceString: I’ve been putting it off all week.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been putting it off all week.

Text.SourceString: Part of being a journalist is being thorough in your investigations.//Some of the topics I pick may not pan out, but the journey of discovery is the most important thing.
Text.LocalizedString: Part of being a journalist is being thorough in your investigations.//Some of the topics I pick may not pan out, but the journey of discovery is the most important thing.

Text.SourceString: When Pufferfish tried to move here, I should have written an article about them and how damaging oil drilling is.//<portrait=concerned>It was a missed opportunity on my part. But maybe it’s not too late.//An article about oil spills might be informative.
Text.LocalizedString: When Pufferfish tried to move here, I should have written an article about them and how damaging oil drilling is.//<portrait=concerned>It was a missed opportunity on my part. But maybe it’s not too late.//An article about oil spills might be informative.

Text.SourceString: Hanging out with you is fun.//You seem well read, and that’s really awesome.
Text.LocalizedString: Hanging out with you is fun.//You seem well read, and that’s really awesome.

Text.SourceString: I feel the need to say this out loud. Here goes nothing… Finishing a good book stresses me out. There.
Text.LocalizedString: I feel the need to say this out loud. Here goes nothing… Finishing a good book stresses me out. There.

Text.SourceString: Well…’cause then, I have to pick a new book to read.//There’s also the worry about whether the new book will be as good as the one I just finished.
Text.LocalizedString: Well…’cause then, I have to pick a new book to read.//There’s also the worry about whether the new book will be as good as the one I just finished.

Text.SourceString: Finished reading a murder mystery last night. Bad idea to stay up for that one.//<portrait=annoyed>I couldn’t sleep until past midnight. Kept thinking I heard something in the kitchen or whatnot…
Text.LocalizedString: Finished reading a murder mystery last night. Bad idea to stay up for that one.//<portrait=annoyed>I couldn’t sleep until past midnight. Kept thinking I heard something in the kitchen or whatnot…

Text.SourceString: It was probably just the wind, right? It was pretty windy last night.
Text.LocalizedString: It was probably just the wind, right? It was pretty windy last night.

Text.SourceString: Oh no! Summer is literally so close. I haven’t set up my reading bingo yet. What should I do, magnificent blue grasshopper?//I know, I know! I need to start tonight, or else it’ll be too late.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh no! Summer is literally so close. I haven’t set up my reading bingo yet. What should I do, magnificent blue grasshopper?//I know, I know! I need to start tonight, or else it’ll be too late.

Text.SourceString: I’m getting my reading bingo ready for Fall.//I’m going to start with a murder mystery! It’s a classic reread from my favorite mystery author, Agatha Christine. Oh, so excited!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m getting my reading bingo ready for Fall.//I’m going to start with a murder mystery! It’s a classic reread from my favorite mystery author, Agatha Christine. Oh, so excited!

Text.SourceString: You look like you’re having a fantastic Sunday, <PlayerName>$player</>!//<portrait=normal>What’s your secret?
Text.LocalizedString: You look like you’re having a fantastic Sunday, <PlayerName>$player</>!//<portrait=normal>What’s your secret?

Text.SourceString: You look like you’re having a fantastic Winter, <PlayerName>$player</>!//<portrait=normal>What’s your secret?
Text.LocalizedString: You look like you’re having a fantastic Winter, <PlayerName>$player</>!//<portrait=normal>What’s your secret?

Text.SourceString: Good thing my house isn’t far from work, because I don’t think I could walk very far in these shoes.
Text.LocalizedString: Good thing my house isn’t far from work, because I don’t think I could walk very far in these shoes.

Text.SourceString: My feet hurt.//<portrait=confused>I think I’ve spent too long standing…
Text.LocalizedString: My feet hurt.//<portrait=confused>I think I’ve spent too long standing…

Text.SourceString: Maybe my feet hurt because I’ve been standing too much today.//It could also be that I need a new pair of shoes.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe my feet hurt because I’ve been standing too much today.//It could also be that I need a new pair of shoes.

Text.SourceString: I can’t see myself being a full-time writer…//<portrait=normal>I like my library job so much I can’t see myself leaving it.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t see myself being a full-time writer…//<portrait=normal>I like my library job so much I can’t see myself leaving it.

Text.SourceString: I’ve been submitting articles to online publications on a pretty consistent basis.//<portrait=normal>There hasn’t been much income from it yet, but I get a lot of satisfaction writing about things I care about.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been submitting articles to online publications on a pretty consistent basis.//<portrait=normal>There hasn’t been much income from it yet, but I get a lot of satisfaction writing about things I care about.

Text.SourceString: It’s the little things in life that matter, right?//<portrait=surprised>That’s the spirit! You sparkly butterfly!
Text.LocalizedString: It’s the little things in life that matter, right?//<portrait=surprised>That’s the spirit! You sparkly butterfly!

Text.SourceString: Oh! You elegant, gullible, slimy cocoon. My glasses aren’t fake.//<portrait=normal>They’re real. I have bad eyesight, and my eyes are too dry for contacts.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh! You elegant, gullible, slimy cocoon. My glasses aren’t fake.//<portrait=normal>They’re real. I have bad eyesight, and my eyes are too dry for contacts.

Text.SourceString: I can’t legally drive without them.//Not that I drive, though.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t legally drive without them.//Not that I drive, though.

Text.SourceString: Today, I spoke with the mayor about our town.//With Winter coming up, we have to be ready for the Winter Fair, snow storms… Winter stuff like that.
Text.LocalizedString: Today, I spoke with the mayor about our town.//With Winter coming up, we have to be ready for the Winter Fair, snow storms… Winter stuff like that.

Text.SourceString: All is good right now.//I’ve spoken to both <NpcName>Joko</> and <NpcName>Rafael</> about these issues as well.//<portrait=normal>You know, get them ready if anything were to go south.
Text.LocalizedString: All is good right now.//I’ve spoken to both <NpcName>Joko</> and <NpcName>Rafael</> about these issues as well.//<portrait=normal>You know, get them ready if anything were to go south.

Text.SourceString: What a joy to see you here, <PlayerName>$player</>!
Text.LocalizedString: What a joy to see you here, <PlayerName>$player</>!

Text.SourceString: Investigative journalism must be thrilling. To be on the front line of world affairs, to pull back the curtain for the public…//<portrait=sad>What I wouldn’t give.
Text.LocalizedString: Investigative journalism must be thrilling. To be on the front line of world affairs, to pull back the curtain for the public…//<portrait=sad>What I wouldn’t give.

Text.SourceString: Though investigative journalism sounds thrilling, it also sounds really scary. Like really, really…//<portrait=concerned>To be on the front line of world affairs, to pull back the curtain for the public…//I don’t know if I’d have it in me.//…
Text.LocalizedString: Though investigative journalism sounds thrilling, it also sounds really scary. Like really, really…//<portrait=concerned>To be on the front line of world affairs, to pull back the curtain for the public…//I don’t know if I’d have it in me.//…

Text.SourceString: I’ve been investigating the old legends of this island, and I found some incredible things! Prepare yourself.//<portrait=surprised>Giants used to live here! Isn’t that amazing?!
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been investigating the old legends of this island, and I found some incredible things! Prepare yourself.//<portrait=surprised>Giants used to live here! Isn’t that amazing?!

Text.SourceString: Apparently, these Giants were small.//They were named for their big, giving hearts… Oh, too out there?
Text.LocalizedString: Apparently, these Giants were small.//They were named for their big, giving hearts… Oh, too out there?

Text.SourceString: I can just talk and talk and talk to you, you effervescent lark.//<portrait=blushing>And you’re cute too.
Text.LocalizedString: I can just talk and talk and talk to you, you effervescent lark.//<portrait=blushing>And you’re cute too.

Text.SourceString: You’re making me nervous…
Text.LocalizedString: You’re making me nervous…

Text.SourceString: The library can be somewhat lonesome. Thank you for visiting, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: The library can be somewhat lonesome. Thank you for visiting, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: Ah! <PlayerName>$player</>, you cultured starling! I must recommend you read <Italic>The Hearth Saga</>.//<portrait=normal>First ten pages, and I’m hooked!
Text.LocalizedString: Ah! <PlayerName>$player</>, you cultured starling! I must recommend you read <Italic>The Hearth Saga</>.//<portrait=normal>First ten pages, and I’m hooked!

Text.SourceString: The library has copies you can check out. It’s gripping.//<portrait=normal>I just know you’ll love it!
Text.LocalizedString: The library has copies you can check out. It’s gripping.//<portrait=normal>I just know you’ll love it!

Text.SourceString: I always love to pass by your farm and see it thriving. You should be proud, <PlayerName>$player</>!
Text.LocalizedString: I always love to pass by your farm and see it thriving. You should be proud, <PlayerName>$player</>!

Text.SourceString: How are you today, my glistening dragonfly?//<portrait=normal>Is there anything I can do for you?
Text.LocalizedString: How are you today, my glistening dragonfly?//<portrait=normal>Is there anything I can do for you?

Text.SourceString: I’ve been submitting articles to online publications on a pretty consistent basis.//<portrait=normal>Not much has come of it yet.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been submitting articles to online publications on a pretty consistent basis.//<portrait=normal>Not much has come of it yet.

Text.SourceString: Still, I get a lot of satisfaction from writing about something that matters to me.
Text.LocalizedString: Still, I get a lot of satisfaction from writing about something that matters to me.

Text.SourceString: You really are lovely, <PlayerName>$player</>. Brave and strong, yet so tender… Ah, how did I get so lucky?
Text.LocalizedString: You really are lovely, <PlayerName>$player</>. Brave and strong, yet so tender… Ah, how did I get so lucky?

Text.SourceString: To think, of all the single people in Starlet Town, you chose me!
Text.LocalizedString: To think, of all the single people in Starlet Town, you chose me!

Text.SourceString: What am I going to do with you, my beautiful lory?
Text.LocalizedString: What am I going to do with you, my beautiful lory?

Text.SourceString: Hey, <PlayerName>$player</>, you look cute! Going somewhere?
Text.LocalizedString: Hey, <PlayerName>$player</>, you look cute! Going somewhere?

Text.SourceString: I’ve read more than my fair share of romance novels, you know.//<portrait=blushing>And now I feel like I’m living in one!
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve read more than my fair share of romance novels, you know.//<portrait=blushing>And now I feel like I’m living in one!

Text.SourceString: I want nothing more than to curl up with a hot drink and a good book tonight…//Ah… Winter nights.
Text.LocalizedString: I want nothing more than to curl up with a hot drink and a good book tonight…//Ah… Winter nights.

Text.SourceString: Can I help you with something, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Can I help you with something, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: The Harvest Festival was a blast! I’m glad the community had fun.//The Sanchez brothers helped us set up the decorations. I don’t know what I’d do without them.
Text.LocalizedString: The Harvest Festival was a blast! I’m glad the community had fun.//The Sanchez brothers helped us set up the decorations. I don’t know what I’d do without them.

Text.SourceString: I’m nervous about the upcoming Tree Planting Festival… I’m scared we may not all fit in the boat.//Let’s hope for the best!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m nervous about the upcoming Tree Planting Festival… I’m scared we may not all fit in the boat.//Let’s hope for the best!

Text.SourceString: I’m so glad the Tree Planting Festival is behind us.//Aside from a couple of people getting seasick, I thought it went pretty well. No boat issues… Nothing!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m so glad the Tree Planting Festival is behind us.//Aside from a couple of people getting seasick, I thought it went pretty well. No boat issues… Nothing!

Text.SourceString: I got all my documents for the upcoming Beach Cleanup Festival.//I need to hire the Sanchez brothers to help us set up the decorations.//<portrait=happy>I’ll talk to them tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: I got all my documents for the upcoming Beach Cleanup Festival.//I need to hire the Sanchez brothers to help us set up the decorations.//<portrait=happy>I’ll talk to them tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: I was just telling <NpcName>Suki</> about the books I’ve been reading… There’s this one particular horror novel. I can’t stand it.//<NpcName>Suki</> doesn’t mind spoilers, ‘cos they’re not her type of books anyway.//She probably won’t read them.
Text.LocalizedString: I was just telling <NpcName>Suki</> about the books I’ve been reading… There’s this one particular horror novel. I can’t stand it.//<NpcName>Suki</> doesn’t mind spoilers, ‘cos they’re not her type of books anyway.//She probably won’t read them.

Text.SourceString: It’s nice here, isn’t it? Away from the town…
Text.LocalizedString: It’s nice here, isn’t it? Away from the town…

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Suki</> and I made sure to bring something for <NpcName>Mr. Takeba</>.//<portrait=concerned>He lives alone, and with all the cleaning up he’s doing to this place, I thought it was the least we could do.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Suki</> and I made sure to bring something for <NpcName>Mr. Takeba</>.//<portrait=concerned>He lives alone, and with all the cleaning up he’s doing to this place, I thought it was the least we could do.

Text.SourceString: But she keeps giving him green smoothies.//They’re unopened in his fridge. I don’t think <NpcName>Mr. Takeba</> likes them very much.
Text.LocalizedString: But she keeps giving him green smoothies.//They’re unopened in his fridge. I don’t think <NpcName>Mr. Takeba</> likes them very much.
